   "source": [
    "# Transformation with Padding\n",
    "\n",
    "To avoid image shrinking, you may opt to pad your array with `np.nan` or other values.\n",
    "We will only discuss with `np.nan`, feel free to adapt to custom padding functions.\n",
    "\n",
    "We achieve padding with `np.pad`"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": "<matplotlib.image.AxesImage at 0x257830fdac0>"
     },
     "execution_count": 5,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>",
      "image/png": "\n"
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from matplotlib import pyplot as plt\n",
    "from matplotlib.image import imread\n",
    "from mpl_toolkits.axes_grid1 import ImageGrid\n",
    "\n",
    "ar = imread(\"../../../data/image.jpg\")[:300:4, :300:4]\n",
    "plt.imshow(ar)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "## Inspection of GLCM Transformation Size"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "GLCM Progress: 100%|██████████| 44.7k/44.7k [00:00<00:00, 233k Cells/s]"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "(75, 75, 3) (61, 61, 3, 7)\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from glcm_cupy import glcm\n",
    "\n",
    "radius = 3\n",
    "step_size = 4\n",
    "g = glcm(ar, bin_from=256, bin_to=16, radius=radius, step_size=step_size)\n",
    "print(ar.shape, g.shape)"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "Notice that the dimensions reduces by `2 * (step_size + radius)`\n",
    "\n",
    "We can counter this by adding `np.nan` around the edges of the image."
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "## Padding with `np.nan`\n",
    "\n",
    "The following is the recipe to pad an image to retain dimension sizes"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "GLCM Progress: 100%|██████████| 67.5k/67.5k [00:00<00:00, 165k Cells/s]"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "(75, 75, 3) (75, 75, 3, 7)\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "padding = radius + step_size\n",
    "ar_pad = np.pad(ar,\n",
    "                pad_width=((padding,), (padding,), (0,)),\n",
    "                constant_values=np.nan)\n",
    "g = glcm(ar_pad, bin_from=256, bin_to=32, radius=radius, step_size=step_size)\n",
    "print(ar.shape, g.shape)"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "## Plot Transformation\n",
    "\n",
    "Notice the behaviour of the transformation with padding, this can cause unnatural artifacts along the edges."
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%% md\n"
    }
   }
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": "Text(0.5, 0.98, 'Padded GLCM Features (Cube Rooted for visibility)')"
     },
     "execution_count": 8,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": "<Figure size 864x576 with 18 Axes>",
      "image/png": "\n"
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Plot in a grid\n",
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))\n",
    "grid = ImageGrid(fig, 111,\n",
    "                 nrows_ncols=(3, 3),\n",
    "                 axes_pad=0.4)\n",
    "\n",
    "for ax, f_ix, title in zip(grid, range(g.shape[-1]),\n",
    "                           (\"HOMOGENEITY\", \"CONTRAST\", \"ASM\", \"MEAN\",\n",
    "                            \"VARIANCE\", \"CORRELATION\", \"DISSIMILARITY\"), ):\n",
    "    ax.imshow(g[:100, :100, :, f_ix] ** (1 / 3))\n",
    "    ax.set_title(title)\n",
    "fig.suptitle('Padded GLCM Features (Cube Rooted for visibility)')"
   ],
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false,
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   }
  }
